constructor.details: Initialize the lease contract. Landlord, tenant, and property details cannot be changed for a contract.

params.landlordAddr: the account address of the landlord
params.propertyLocation: the location of the property being leased out
params.propertyName: the name of the property being leased out
params.tenantAddr: the account address of the tenant

depositSecurityDeposit().details: The tenant can deposit money for the security deposit to activate the lease

evict().details: Called by landlord if the tenant hasn't met the terms of the lease

payRent().details: The tenant can deposit money for the security deposit to activate the lease

setTerms(uint256,uint256,uint256,uint256.details: Set the terms for lease. Can be called by the tenant or the landlord while the lease is inactive.

params.latePenaltyPerDay: late penalty per day in Wei
params.rentalDuration: length of lease agreement in months
params.startDate: start date of the agreement (as a unix timestamp)

signAgreement().details: The tenant or landlord can accept the agreement.  Both parties have to agree for the contract to be put in active state.

unsignAgreement().details: The tenant or landlord can revoke their agreement to the lease while the lease is inactive.

vacate().details: Called when the tenant wants to leave the house. This is provided the terms of the lease have been met. Security deposit is transferred back

arguments.value: Only landlord or tenant should b
e allowed to create the lease.
